## S 3. Retry After no_dialog Failure

🚨 **Use ONLY when S 5 (Reply/Comment Flow) returns `no_dialog` after a successful S 2 click.**

The activity page popup can intermittently fail to open even though the click registered. When this happens:

1. **NEVER navigate to the post URL** — on post pages, `icons[0]` is the original post's Reply button, NOT the comment thread reply. Clicking it posts a top-level comment instead of a threaded reply.
2. Instead, re-navigate to the activity page and retry once:

```javascript
// Step 1: Navigate back to activity/replies (resets page state)
browser.act({
  kind: "navigate",
  url: "https://www.threads.net/activity/replies",
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})

// Step 2: Wait 3s for page load, then run S 2 again with the same allowedIds
// (use the S 2 code above with the failing postId still in allowedIds)

// Step 3: If S 2 returns clicked=true, run S 5 again
// Step 4: If S 5 still returns no_dialog → SKIP this post, move to next
```

**Never retry more than once per post.** If the popup fails twice, skip and move on.
